mayor-layla: "So, you've made Bael lower his prices, eh?" "Well, at least no one's dying of thirst anymore." "But you should see them, adventurer." "The town's folk, they're stumbling around drunk more often than not." "The kids, they're crying because their parents are sick or can't work." "I just hope this was the right thing to do." "Anyway, here's something for your efforts."